<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-03-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-03-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="470" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d470">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Powell</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-03-17"><hi rend="italic">March 17,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 677.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 1657, of the 21st ultimo, reporting the use of your unofficial good
                            offices on behalf of certain Syrians whose expulsion was ordered from
                            Haiti without a sufficient time being granted them to enable them to
                            dispose of their stocks of goods.</p>
                        <p>The use of your unofficial good offices in their behalf is approved.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>